    <h4>About</h4>
    <p>Cunxi is an Assistant Professor in the ECE Department (A. James Clark
                                                School of Engineering), and an
                                                affiliated Assistant Professor
                                                in the CS Department, at the
                                                <a href="https://umd.edu">University of
                                                  Maryland, College Park</a>. His research interests focus on novel algorithms, systems, and hardware designs for computing and security. Before joining University of Maryland, Cunxi was Assistant Professor with University of Utah, and held PostDoc at Cornell University (with <a
 href="http://www.csl.cornell.edu/~zhiruz/index.html">Prof. Zhiru Zhang</a>) and EPFL in 2017-2018 (with <a
 href="http://si2.epfl.ch/~demichel/">Prof. Giovanni De Micheli</a>). Cunxi was a research intern at IBM T.J Watson Research Center in 2015
 and 2016. He received Ph.D. degree from UMass Amherst in 2017 under <a
 href="http://www.ecs.umass.edu/ece/labs/vlsicad/ciesielski.html">Prof. Maciej
 Ciesielski</a>. His work received the Best Paper Award at ASPLOS (2025), Best Paper Award at DAC (2023), Best Paper Finalists at DAC (2025), Best Paper Nomination at ICCAD (2025), and several other Best Paper Nominations, NVIDIA Academic Research Award (2025), First Place of DAC Hack@DAC (2017), American Physical Society DLS poster award (2022), and NSF
 CAREER Award (2021). 
